
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `fonttosfnt` yek dastoor baraye tabdil format-haye font be format SFNT ast. SFNT yek format standard baraye font-ha ast, ke dar system-amel-haye mokhtalef mesle Windows va macOS estefade mishavad. In dastoor bishtar baraye kar ba font-haye ba format-haye ghadimi ya ghair-standard be kar miravad ta anha ra compatible ba system-haye jadid konad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `-l`  --> 🗂️ List kardane format-haye font-e support shode. Baraye fahmidan che format-haee ghabele tabdil hastand.
    🔹 `-o <file>`  --> 💾 Specify kardane name file khoruji. Agar in gozine estefade nashavad, file khoruji bar rooye stdout neveshte mishavad.
    🔹 `-v`  --> 📢 Namayesh etela'at bishtar dar morede process tabdil (verbose mode).

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ fonttosfnt input.otf -o output.ttf

    🔹 Tabdil file `input.otf` be file `output.ttf` (OpenType be TrueType).

    $ fonttosfnt -l

    🔹 List kardane hameye format-haye font-e support shode.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ fonttosfnt myfont.pfb -o myfont.ttf

    🔹 Tabdil yek font PostScript Type 1 (PFB) be TrueType (TTF). In kar baraye estefade az font dar system-amel-haee ke faghat TrueType support mikonand mofid ast.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `fonttosfnt` command is used to convert font formats to the SFNT format. SFNT is a standard font format used in various operating systems such as Windows and macOS. This command is primarily used to work with fonts in older or non-standard formats to make them compatible with modern systems.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `-l`  --> 🗂️ List supported font formats. Useful for understanding which formats can be converted.
    🔹 `-o <file>`  --> 💾 Specify the output file name. If this option is not used, the output is written to stdout.
    🔹 `-v`  --> 📢 Display more information about the conversion process (verbose mode).

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ fonttosfnt input.otf -o output.ttf

    🔹 Convert the `input.otf` file to the `output.ttf` file (OpenType to TrueType).

    $ fonttosfnt -l

    🔹 List all supported font formats.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ fonttosfnt myfont.pfb -o myfont.ttf

    🔹 Convert a PostScript Type 1 font (PFB) to TrueType (TTF). This is useful for using the font in operating systems that only support TrueType.
